
<purchabr>SALE TILNEY</purchabr> BUYS STAKE IN U.S. INSURANCE BROKER
    LONDON, March 2 - {<purchaser>Sale Tilney Plc</purchaser>} said it has <status>purchased</status>
80 pct of the ordinary share capital of {<acquired>B and R International
Inc.</acquired>}, a <acqloc>U.S.</acqloc> <acqbus>Insurance</acqbus> broker, for <dlramt>5.6 mln dlrs</dlramt>.
    <purchabr>Sale</purchabr> is paying 3.6 mln dlrs in cash on completion, with the
balance plus interest to be paid in equal instalments over the
next six years.
    <acqabr>B and R</acqabr> posted pretax profit of 855,000 dlrs in the year to
Dec 31, 1986 when it had net tangible assets of 563,000 dlrs.
